-- Multi-step LLM reasoning chain

cell topic
  yield subject = the trolley problem

cell define
  given topic.subject
  yield definition
  ---
  Define «subject» in exactly two sentences. Be precise and academic.
  ---

cell argue-for
  given topic.subject
  given define.definition
  yield argument
  ---
  Given this definition of «subject»: «definition». Write a compelling argument FOR the utilitarian position (pull the lever). Three sentences max.
  ---

cell argue-against
  given topic.subject
  given define.definition
  yield argument
  ---
  Given this definition of «subject»: «definition». Write a compelling argument AGAINST pulling the lever (deontological position). Three sentences max.
  ---

cell synthesize
  given argue-for.argument
  given argue-against.argument
  yield synthesis
  ---
  You have two arguments about the trolley problem. FOR pulling the lever: «argument». AGAINST pulling the lever: «argument». Write a balanced two-sentence synthesis that acknowledges both positions without taking a side.
  ---
  check synthesis is not empty
